'''Svetlana Alexandrovna Pletneva''' (also called ''Pletnyeva'' and ''Pletnyova'' {{lang-ru|Светлана Александровна Плетнева}}) (April 1, 1926 in [[Kirov, Kirov Oblast|Vyatka]]- 20 November 2008 in [[Moscow]]) was a [[Russia]]n and [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] [[archaeologist]] and [[historian]]. Like [[Lev Gumilev]], she was a student of [[Mikhail Illarionovich Artamonov|Mikhail Artamonov]], although she discarded many of the former's theories as mere speculations. She won the [[USSR State Prize]] in 1986

Pletneva is the author of numerous books on [[Eurasia]]n [[nomads]], particularly the [[Khazars]].

